@Node INTR "Introduction to this PowerDOOR"

  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
                        Introduction - What is it?
  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

   Power Send is a Door that replaces the MAXsBBS Internal Function 16
   which is the Send Message Function. After being on Fluffynet for
   a while and other Nets, I found that whilst scanning through the
   Mail, I found Messages for myself addressed to the wrong person or
   Spelt incorrectly.
 
   This Door features one of the features that MAXsBBS was originally
   bereft of. It features a great `SysOp' Mail Diversion system which
   will automatically redirect mail addressed to `SysOp' to whoever
   is specified in the `Send' configuration...

   This Door brings up a Normal `Who is the Message For?' requester
   but this time, It gives the user the choice to press [RETURN] on
   a Blank line to activate the Search List.

   The User can now use the cursor keys as well as the previous versions
   `<' and `>' keys to search through the list of Users for the User
   they want. A small description of the User is provided to aid in
   the Search. When the relevant person is found, Simply press [RETURN]
   and hopefully...

   The Message will be sent...

  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
                        What does this Door offer?
  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
  
   This Door offers a unique User Listing system that allows the User
   to select who he/she wants to send a message to...

   They can also press any Letter key and the System will jump to the
   next name in the list with the same first letter as that pressed.

   This Door also offers a unique User-Base to User-List Conversion
   System which converts your MAXsBBS `User.Data' User-Base file into
   a List that is compatible for use with PowerSEND.

   @{" [0] " Link MAIN} Return to the Main Menu

@EndNode INTR

@Node INST "Installing PowerDOORS"

  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
                     Installation of this PowerDOOR...
  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

   All PowerDOORS are installed in the same way. Simply, make sure that
   there is a directory in your Doors directory or assignment called
   `POWER'. This is where all PowerDOORS are stored. If you do not have
   your DOORS directory assigned, then you should add an Assign to your
   Startup-Sequence or User-Startup File.

        C:Assign >NIL: DOORS: BBS:Doors/
                              ^^^^^^^^^^
                              Change this to your Doors directory path

   Now, Create a directory inside the `DOORS:Power/' Directory with
   the name of the Door. This is the word to the right of the `Power'
   in the Archive filename. So, For example, if the PowerDOOR was called
   PowerSEND, then you would create a directory in the `DOORS:Power/'
   directory called `SEND'.

   Now, Locate the Archive you downloaded or received. It will probably
   be in the `LhA' or `LZX' form. Simply use a version of `LhA' or `LZX'
   to Extract the files into the desired path.

    C:LhA x PowerSEND_??.LHA DOORS:Power/RawUL/  \  Where `????' is the
                                                  } Name of the PowerDOOR
    C:LZX x PowerSEND_??.LZX DOORS:Power/RawUL/  /  For example, `SEND'

   Now, all the files including some File Descriptions `File_ID.DIZ' and
   some Configuration files `Send.CFG'. Other files will also be
   included which are not Doors such as those that have the File
   Extension of `.Text'. These files are ANSIs. If you find a file with
   an extension of `DAT', then do not try and edit these.

   Now, Go through all your MAXsBBS Menus and look for every entry that
   has Function `16' setup. This is a `Send Message' Command. Now,
   Change that `16' to `34'. Now, in the `Filename/Path' box, Enter in
   the path of PowerSEND followed by the Section Number where the
   Message is to be posted and then by the List to be used.

   Key   Function   Extra   Lo Acc   Hi Acc   Path/Filename
   ~~~   ~~~~~~~~   ~~~~~   ~~~~~~   ~~~~~~   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~
     ?         34       0        ?        ?   POWER:Send/Send <PARAMETERS>

   Where <PARAMETERS> should consist of a TWO DIGIT Number followed by
   a Space followed by another TWO DIGIT NUMBER...

   ie.  POWER:Send/Send XX YY

   Where `XX' represents the Section Number for the message to be
   posted in. But make sure that `XX' is Two digits long, So for
   example, `9' would become `09' and so on...

   And, `YY' represents the `User-List' for PowerSEND to use. This
   means that you can automatically load the Fluffynet User-List for
   all your Fluffynet Menus... Also, `YY' should also be TWO DIGITS.
   So, `9' would become `09'...

   Remember, BOTH the Section Number and List Number must consist of
   TWO DIGIT NUMBERS. So, If the Number is only a Single Digit,
   `1', `3' etc, then you should place a ZERO `0' before it to make
   a DOUBLE DIGIT... `01' or `03' etc.

   @{" [0] " Link MAIN} Return to the Main Menu

@EndNode INST

@Node CONF "Configuring PowerDOORS"

  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
                       Configuration of PowerDOORS
  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

   All PowerDOORS are configured in the same way. In the PowerDOOR
   archive (or Directory if extracted), You will find file(s) with an
   extension of `.CFG', These are @{b}C@{ub}on@{b}F@{ub}i@{b}G@{ub}uration files.

   Simply load these Configuration (CFG) Files into a Text Editor and
   either follow the simple guide located at the end of the Configuration
   files or use the more complex guide which is located in the Door Guide.

  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
    Layout for the Configuration                               PowerSend
  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

  << @{b}Line 01@{ub} >> - @{i} Path & Filename @{ui}
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   This line should contain the Path and Filename for the Main ANSI
   File that is displayed during the Doors usage. Check the included
   ANSI File `Send.Text' for the Table and positioning Layout.

  << @{b}Line 02@{ub} >> - @{i} Path & Filename @{ui}
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   This line should contain the Path and Filename for the ANSI that
   contains information on the Keyboard Shortcuts used in PowerSEND.
   This ANSI is the Help File. Check the included File `Help.Text'
   for the available Keyboard Shortcuts.

   (Note: [<-],[->],[/\],[\/] represent Cursor Keys L,R,U and D)

  << @{b}Line 03@{ub} >> - @{i} Number @{ui}
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   This line should contain a Number that represents the Y coordinate
   on which the Doors Status information will be centred on.

   By default this is set to `20', so the Door Information and Status
   details will appear centred on Line 20 (at the bottom of the screen)

  << @{b}Line 04@{ub} >> - @{i} User Name @{ui}
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   This line should contain the Name of the BBS SysOp. This is the
   name at which mail addressed to `SysOp' is diverted to, So double
   check spelling etc. as otherwise you may lose a bit of mail.

  << @{b}Line 05@{ub} >> - @{i} List Selection Boolean @{ui}
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   This line should contain either a `YES', `Y', `TRUE' or `1' or a
   `NO', `N', `FALSE' or `0'. This is an option which allows the
   User to be able to use the Left and Right Cursor Keys as well as
   the Number keys (1-9), to select a User-List to use, but if you
   want to force the Users to use only ONE User List specified in
   the Command Line of the Door Path, Please set this to a Negative
   Value (ie. NO, FALSE or 0). If you want Users to be able to choose
   which list, Make this value a Positive one (ie. YES, TRUE or 1).

  << @{b}Line 06@{ub} >> - @{i} End of Configuration @{ui}
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   As with all PowerDOORS, The Hash (#) at the end of the Configuration
   signifies its end. Any text after this Hash (either to the right or
   below it) will be ignored by the Door making it useful to add comments
   about the configuration below.
   
  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

   Now, Save the Configuration File as a Plain ASCII File and not a
   Wordworth or other WP Document. Make sure that the File is saved in
   Plain ASCII otherwise it will not work.

  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

   With PowerSEND, You can have upto 9 List configurations, These are
   called `List.CFG.?' where `?' is a number from 1 to 9. Now, These
   files contain the Users and Descriptions.

   The First Line should contain a Description of the User-List such as
   `Fluffy Net - The Users from Fluffy Net' or something like that.

   The rest of the lines should contain the `Name' of the User, then on
   the next line, the `Description' of the User...

   Example File
   ~~~~~~~~~~~~
    Fluffy Net User List - The Peepz from the Land of Fluffy
    Niki Murkett
    SysOp of Redrum BBS
    Steve Clack
    SysOp of Total Eclipse BBS
    Techn!x
    SysOp of Sub-Bass BBS

   @{" [0] " Link MAIN} Return to the Main Menu

@EndNode CONF

@Node USIN "Using the PowerDOOR"

  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
                           Using the PowerDOOR...
  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

   The Main Door - `SEND'
   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   When the Door is loaded, The Main ANSI Screen will appear asking you
   to enter in the Destination (Name) of the User who you want to send
   a message to.

   You can either:-

    i)  Enter in the Name of the User and press [RETURN], The door will
        now exit and the BBS will return on the `Enter Subject' Prompt.

 or...  You can simply press [RETURN] without entering a name...

   After a short while, The User Database will load and all the Users
   contained in the Database will appear. Now, You will see the Names
   of the Users on the Left hand side of the screen.

   Using either the `<' `[' and `>' `]' keys, or the Cursor Keys,
   You can scroll up and down the list to search for the relevant user.
   The Selected User will be displayed in White at the top of the list.
   A brief description of the selected user will be displayed on the
   Status line.

   You use the Cursor Keys `/\' and `\/' to search through the Users
   but as from Version 1.3, You can use the Cursor Keys `<' and `>'
   to cycle through the available User-Lists. These are the Lists that
   contain the User details. Included in the PowerSEND archive are two
   example Configurations `List.CFG.1', `List.CFG.2' and `List.CFG.3'.

   When you have found the right user, Simply press [RETURN] and the
   Door will exit to the BBS at the `Enter Subject' prompt. Now,
   Continue as you would when sending a message...

   You can search for a specific user by using the `#' Hash key.
   Simply press the Hash (#) key and the `TO:' prompt will change
   to a `SEARCH:' prompt. Now, Enter the first few letters of the
   name and the System will search for that user...

   So, entering `Nik' would find... `Niki Murkett'

   NOTE: As from Version 1.2, You will not be able to send a message
         to yourself as the Door checks your User Name and if you
         try to send a message to that user-name using either the
         Text box or the Listing method, You will get a message
         saying that you can't post a message to yourself.

   NOTE: As from Version 1.5, PowerSEND uses MAXsBBS Text lines 51 and
         264 which are `Send Message to:...' and 'You cannot Send Mail
         to Yourself!'. Please feel free to change theses to ANSI Files
         using the `<BBS:Text/Example.Text' method as it does make the
         Door look better.

   Alternatively, You can simply press any Letter (A-Z) key and the
   System will automatically jump to the next name that starts with
   the letter you pressed. Once you have reached the last entry that
   begins with the letter key you pressed, The system will jump back
   to the top.

   When you are in the Listing mode, You can press the `?' Question Mark
   key to obtain Online Help on the available Keyboard Shortcuts.

   To exit from the `List' mode back to the `Enter Destination'
   prompt, Simply press either the Backspace Key or the [SPACE] Bar.

   You can exit back to the BBS at any time by pressing the [ESCAPE]
   Key. This will perform a FINISH command which will Exit immediately
   back to the BBS without no copyright or credits appearing.

   The User-Base Converter - `UBConvert'
   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   To create a PowerSEND User-List containing all the Users on your BBS
   simply run the `UBConvert' tool from Workbench and NOT from MAXsBBS
   as `UBConvert' is a Utility and not a Door.

   Now, You will be presented by a WB Window containing some gadgets...
   Below is a list of the Gadgets and what they do or represent...

   User File:   This is the Path and Filename of your MAXsBBS User
                Database File. This is usually called `User.Data' and
                is usually found in `BBS:UserFiles/'. You can select
                the File using a File Requester by clicking on the
                `[F]' gadget to the right of the String gadget.

   List CFG:    This is the Path and Filename of the PowerSEND List
                CFG File that you want to create. The File should be
                located in `DOORS:Power/Send/' and should be called
                `List.CFG.?' where `?' is a number from 1 to 9.
                Again, Clicking on the `[F]' gadget to the right of
                the String Gadget will bring up a File Requester.

   CFG Desc:    This is the Description of the User List File. This
                should be a brief description of what the File
                contains. Examples include `Sub-Bass BBS Users' or
                `Redrum Peepz'.

   Def Desc:    This should be a short description given to all Users
                contained in the User List. Examples include
                `Sub-Bass User' or `Redrum Peep'.

   Generate:    Once you have completed all the relevant text boxes
                and ONLY after that (as this Button will not work
                unless the `CFG Desc' and `Def Desc' are not empty.)
                You can click on the [GENERATE] button. This will load
                in the User-Base File and then Write out the Power
                Send List Configuration File.

   Cancel:      This Gadget will Close UBConvert without saving any
                changes.

   @{" [0] " Link MAIN} Return to the Main Menu

@EndNode USIN

