@Node HIST "The History of this Door..."

  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
                          History of this Door
  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

    Version 2.2 (9th May 1997)
    ~~~~~~~~~~~
   O - Corrected Some minor bugs such as if you entered in your
       First Name, and then pressed [RETURN] it would think that
       you were talking to yourself.

   O - Added Option to add a List Number in the Doors Command Line
       to specify which List.CFG to use.

    Version 2.0 (5th May 1997)
    ~~~~~~~~~~~
   O - Added `UBConvert' which converts the MAXsBBS User-Database
       File `File.Data' to a PowerSEND List Configuration File.

   O - Sorted some Minor Bugs...

   O - Recompiled it with the New GUI Extension (v1.6a)

    Version 1.9 (1st May 1997)
    ~~~~~~~~~~~
   O - Corrected Assignment Bug in all PowerDOORS

    Version 1.8 (29th April 1997)
    ~~~~~~~~~~~
   O - Made the User-List area shorter (Now 5 lines high). This has
       led to major speed increases in Door operation. The increases
       can be upto 4 times faster than version 1.7

    Version 1.7 (20th April 1997)
    ~~~~~~~~~~~
   O - As from 20th April 1997, All PowerDOORS have been Patched with
       Niki Murkett's `Multitasking' Patch System to allow usage on
       Multi-Node BBS's.

    Version 1.6 (31st March 1997) - "Two New Versions in One Day!"
    ~~~~~~~~~~~
   O - Added Shortcuts [1] to [9] for selecting User-Lists.

   O - Added [0] Zero Key to add current User to the Global List (1)

    Version 1.5 (31st March 1997)
    ~~~~~~~~~~~
   O - Replaced in-built `Enter Message To:' and `You Cannot Send Mail
       to Yourself` Messages with the MAXsBBS Internal Text Editor
       Lines (51 & 264) to make Style of PowerSEND for suitable to
       many BBS's.

   O - Enhanced Code to prevent ANSI Screen Redraws after User-List
       selected using Cursor Keys.
    
    Version 1.4 (29th March 1997)
    ~~~~~~~~~~~
   O - Added Search Facility to allow quick searches for Users.

   O - Added the `SysOp' diversion system which diverts messages
       addressed to `SysOp' to the correct name, ie. `Techn!x'

   O - Added FluffyNet and Developers User-Lists to archive.

    Version 1.3 (28th March 1997)
    ~~~~~~~~~~~
   O - Added Multiple User Lists and optimised Cursor routines.

   O - Speeded up Scrolling System by eliminating Error Checking.

   O - Configuration File Changed to accomodate new Help ANSI File
       which is accessed by pressing `?' in the Main Door.

    Version 1.2 (26th March 1997)
    ~~~~~~~~~~~
   O - Corrected Cursor Key procedure. Cursor Up Key made the list
       scroll down and Vice Versa. So, Had to change that before
       Public Release.

   O - Added `Aminet' Readme files as well as `File_ID.DIZ' files to
       all PowerDOOR Archives.

   O - Sorted Introduction Bug out. The `Version' String at the Start
       was corrupt, so the AmigaDOS `Version' command would not
       recognise the Version string.
       It should be `PowerSEND (Mail Destinator) v?.?'.
    
    Version 1.1 (25th March 1997)
    ~~~~~~~~~~~
   O - Added Cursor Key Support to make the Door easier to use.
    
    Version 1.0 (21st March 1997)
    ~~~~~~~~~~~
   O - Removed Description Column as it slowed the Door down to much.

   @{" [0] " Link MAIN} Return to the Main Menu

